            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/c6b43ad861391ea7/text/000000861",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-c6b43ad861391ea7-0d454f twpub-c6b43ad861391ea7-5fae15 twpub-c6b43ad861391ea7-1a3ef0 twpub-c6b43ad861391ea7-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"back\"><div class=\"div1 notes\"><div class=\"divBody\"><p><sup><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/c6b43ad861391ea7/text/000000164\">259</$link></sup> Probably the abacá, although it may be the cloth made from the palm. See Morga’s description of the Visayans, <span class=\"sc\">Vol. XVI</span>, p. 112.</p></div></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/c6b43ad861391ea7/text/000000862": {
