        "$:/plugins/twpub/c6b43ad861391ea7/text/000001548": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/c6b43ad861391ea7/text/000001548",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-c6b43ad861391ea7-0d454f twpub-c6b43ad861391ea7-5fae15 twpub-c6b43ad861391ea7-1a3ef0 twpub-c6b43ad861391ea7-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"back\"><div class=\"div1 notes\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><p class=\"footnote\"><span class=\"label\"><$link class=\"noteref pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/c6b43ad861391ea7/text/000000324\">73</$link></span> This man was Shanghaied at the island of Teneriffe by order of Magalhães, October 1, 1519, and embarked on the “Santiago,” but his occupation or country is unknown. He returned in the “Victoria,” and was one of those captured by the Portuguese in the island of Santiago in the Cape Verde Islands, as is proved by documents in Archivo General de Indias.—Navarrete.</p></div></div></div></div>"
        },
